ghadja</hi> (<ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.languages#L.824">
türk</ref>.) ‘Hirtenpfeife‘. <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.languages#L.779">Span</ref>., <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.languages#L.844">portg</ref>. <hi rend="unknown" rendition="#none">gaita</hi> Schuchardt, Slav.-D. und Slav.-Rom. 42.“ (<bibl>
                     <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.bibliography#BIBL.1294">
Meyer-Lübke 1911</ref>: 280</bibl>)</note>
               <hi rend="unknown" rendition="#none">Berneker</hi>
